// // (f && !b && (d == Once.ready)) ==> (v == 1) || (v == 0) && (2)
// // (f && (d == Once.done)) ==> ((v < -1) || (v > 1))          (3)
// // Case 1: Neither thread has set the flag yet; it is still in init. state
// // Case 2: The flag has been set, but the interferer thread has not yet been blocked.
// //         The interferer thread may have written the value as 2
// // Case 3: The flag is set, and the interferer has been blocked.
// //         The value has been set, and other threads can see the signal with
// //         (d) that it is done.
